column5: Well i was just wondering where everyone is fishing this long weekend,  im not to sure yet but the forecast looks great right now for southern ontario,so i think its gonna be some walleye & muskie fishing for me..  ...be safe and have a great thanksgiving   cheers.....
Dunnville Friday for walleye,Saturday / Sunday local (on the Grand) for smallies and hope to visit my Bro in Niagara Falls and try the river for whatever is in the mood
Gonna be fishing Simcoe in an attempt to catch some Football Smallies and then I might try for salmon at the nottawasaga river.

Goin down to the GOM next week after some Salty denizens of the deep... if the weather will cooperate.  May be another OFNer or two down there as well...  Hope I remember the camera and the batteries don't die eh?

The Sturgeon River ,the Veuve River and Nipissing on Saturday for Walleye and Muskies, Sunday i'll tow into Dokis 45 Minutes away and fish Nipissing and the French River for some Big Pike and Muskies. Should be interesting..
Closing/winterizing my Trailer on Pigeon Lake, and a few days of Muskie fishing as well.
Katchewanooka for our annual fishing trip, or as I like to "Strss Management Weekend"
Up in the Kawarthas Balsam or Gull for some Largies & Walleye
Friday - Lake O or LSC Saturday - LSC or Lake O Sunday - Lake Huron
~~~~Will be out phishen the Yankees, on Simcoe, on Sunday and Monday, for Perch

I have yet to decide where I am heading. I am considering fishing the buffalo harbor for the weekend, for muskies. There is a possibility that I will fish LSC also. I am leaning towards going to the Cornwall area and fishing Lake St.Francis with my brother for muskies and also the ottawa river area too.
Not sure yet Shawn.  We'll probably pound the shores locally.  We're having the family over for Thanksgiving dinner on Sunday so we'll be prepping Saturday and Sunday.  Have a great weekend Shawn!
Sat, where is still yet too be decided.. With whom is yet too be decided. But with a day pass from the warden I am going fishing  before she changes her mind.
This is probably going to be the last short-sleeved weekend folks so, make it count. I'll be taking a shot at Sorel/Tracy for walleye.  Maybe if I rig for walleye I'll get a few pickerel too.
georgian bay somewhere for the toothy critters.  turkey in a can for us!
There are no toothy critters in GB!!
lol squid.  what makes you say that?  we've done well this year

Saturday on the Grand for Smallies, Sunday or Monday anywhere I can dip a line is fine (is it bad to bail on a turkey dinner being given in your own home because you'd rather be fishing?)  Have a great weekend everyone.
well i not sure but i guess fishing for toothy critters on Sturgeon lake won't be a stretch, then maybe I'll try out my turkey deep fryer and if i goof on that i have lots of hamburgers
leaving at 5:30 Saturday morning for the north end of Pigeon, Sunday or Monday I'd like to hit Georgian Bay for some musky if the winds are not to bad.
maybe some musky fishing for me up at  the chalet( st agathe des monts) after i get my snowmobile for my first ride in 3 weeks lol
well normally we hit the niner and maitland for some salmon and bows but since the tribs are bone dry we are going to try LSC for some eyes and musky

I'll be fishing 12 Mile Lake up near Haliburton all weekend looking for some bronze footballs. If/when the mood strikes, I might go to another lake for 'skis and/or pike. Looks like its going to be a beautiful weekend!!!
Fishing??? Thats passe.... lol... NOW Hunting with your Honey.. thats the new trend!!!
Before you do that, you need to think. When was the last time I ticked her off?... and how ticked was she? Has she really forgotten about it by now???  Think about it!
